{
  "texts": [
    "This generally makes the model less prone to 'overfitting', a phenomenon whereby a model may perform very well on training data but poorly on new, unseen data.",
    "Supervised methods have widespread applications with tabular (i.e., numerical or categorical) outcomes in ART.",
    "ANNs are networks of connected computational units representing artificial neurons-they receive inputs, process them, and signal the result to other neurons connected to them, in a multilayered structure (e.g., the multi-layer perceptron algorithm).",
    "The input layer receives data to be processed, and the output layer presents the model output.",
    "The strengths ('weights') of connections between artificial neurons comprise the parameters of the ANN and are calibrated during model training."
  ]
}